            "__cdata": "<p class=\"p_20\">4. A patient at 8 weeks of gestation complains of mild vaginal bleeding. On examination, os is closed and brownish discharge is present in the vagina. The abdomen is soft, non-tender and no guarding was noted. She denies passage of any tissue. USG findings show the gestational age to be 7wks. Diagnosis?</p>"
